        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 12:31AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1231 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Postell to Jack Brown Estates to Marshallville,
and moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph, frequent lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Macon, Fort Valley, Byron, Marshallville, Payne, Payne City, Saint
Louis, Nakomis, Jack Brown Estates, Rutland, Clinton, Cross Keys,
Wesleyan, Powerville, Lizella, Skipperton, Lee Pope, Winchester, and
Miami Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
